# Trapeza project rules

## Before large changes

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md](../../SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md).
Check the tail of [IMPLEMENTATION-LOG.md](../../IMPLEMENTATION-LOG.md) for current status.
Check [ACTIVITY-LOG.md](../../ACTIVITY-LOG.md) for recent sessions on this branch.

## Security

- Never commit `.env`, private keys, or Circle API secrets.
- Arc **testnet only** unless explicitly instructed otherwise.

## Module boundary

- `@trapeza/core` (`packages/core/`) must stay chain-agnostic: no viem, no Circle SDK, no UI, no MCP.
- All Circle/Arc/on-chain code lives in `packages/adapter-arc/` or `packages/adapter-gateway/`.
- App layer (`apps/`) imports only `@trapeza/core` public API.

## Arc / Circle integration

Before adapter or on-chain work, read the matching skill from
`context-for-agent/docs/circlefin-skills/`. Full routing table: `context-for-agent/AGENTS.md`.

When copying patterns, check `context-for-agent/samples/` as **read-only reference** — do not
modify sample repos in place.

Prefer local bundled docs (`context-for-agent/docs/`) first. Use live MCP servers
(`arc-docs`, `circle` in `.cursor/mcp.json`) when local docs are insufficient.

## Up-to-date documentation

Do not rely on training data alone for API signatures, config keys, or version-specific behavior.

- **Third-party libraries/SDKs** (viem, vitest, TypeScript, OR-Tools, `@circle-fin/x402-batching`, etc.):
  query **Context7** MCP (`user-context7`: `resolve-library-id` then `query-docs`) before writing or changing integration code.
- **Context7 miss or stale docs:** use **web search** for changelogs, migrations, or recent fixes.
- **Arc/Circle product docs:** local bundle → `arc-docs` / `circle` MCP → web search.
- Always look up docs when adding a new dependency or debugging SDK/version errors.

## On-chain work

- Follow [SETUP.md](../../SETUP.md) for wallet funding and env vars.
- Spike scripts must print real tx hashes from observed receipts — never fabricate.

## Logging

- **Every session that modifies files:** append an [ACTIVITY-LOG.md](../../ACTIVITY-LOG.md) entry before finishing.
- **Milestones / spikes / blockers:** also update [IMPLEMENTATION-LOG.md](../../IMPLEMENTATION-LOG.md).
- Author: ask the user for their handle if unknown; default Mode to `assisted`.
- Never log secrets; never fabricate verification results.

## Verification

After core changes: `npm run typecheck && npm test`.
